This paper is about machine learning and probabilistic modeling, which suggests it belongs to the category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper specifically focuses on variational inference, which is a common technique in machine learning for approximating complex probability distributions. This suggests that cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) may also be a relevant category. The paper also discusses the use of stratified sampling, which is a technique commonly used in computer vision (cs.CV) and statistics (cs.ST). Finally, the paper introduces a new lower bound on the evidence, which is a concept from information theory (cs.IT).
